20Travel%20Portal%20User''s%20Manual.docx#_Toc391966709">Resources. 14</a>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <a href="file:///C:/Users/561706/Desktop/IREMS/Web%20Travel%20Portal%20User''s%20Manual.docx#_Toc391966710">Screen Options. 15</a>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <a href="file:///C:/Users/561706/Desktop/IREMS/Web%20Travel%20Portal%20User''s%20Manual.docx#_Toc391966711">+New.. 16</a>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <a href="file:///C:/Users/561706/Desktop/IREMS/Web%20Travel%20Portal%20User''s%20Manual.docx#_Toc391966712">New Post. 16</a>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <a href="file:///C:/Users/561706/Desktop/IREMS/Web%20Travel%20Portal%20User''s%20Manual.docx#_Toc391966713">New Media. 17</a>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966698">Login &amp; Registration</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Go to dev.webtravelportal.net.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        2. Enter your credentials if you current have an account with the Web Travel Portal\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p align="center">\r\n        <img width="360" height="565" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <p>\r\n        3. Select “Register” if you need to create a new account with the Web Travel Portal.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p align="center">\r\n        <br/>\r\n        <img width="325" height="720" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <h2>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966699">Email Confirmation</a>\r\n    </h2>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="191" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966700">Dashboard</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Once successfully logged in, the following dashboard will appear.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="317" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        2. From the Dashboard, you make your selection.\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966701">Help Options</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. For help options, select “help” at the top right corner of the dashboard.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="863" height="143" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966702">User Profile</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Select “Edit Profile” in the top right corner of the Dashboard.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p align="center">\r\n        <img width="286" height="200" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        2. View your Profile.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="399" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966703">Travel Portal Homepage</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Select “Travel Portal” in the top right of the webpage.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="373" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966704">New Travel Request</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Locate the “Travel Requests” drop-down menu in the center of the page.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        2. Select “New Travel Request.”\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="694" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        3. You have the option of saving your current request and finish at another time or selecting next to continue through the process.\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966705">Extras</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        a) Select “Extras” in the center of the page.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        b) From this drop-down menu, the user is able to view trip reports and official travel letters.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="268" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h2>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966706">Trip Report</a>\r\n    </h2>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Under the “Extras” drop-down menu, you will see two options.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        a) The first option will be “Trip Report.”\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="447" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h2>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966707">Official Travel Letter</a>\r\n    </h2>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. Under the “Extras” drop-down menu, you will see two options.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        a) The first option will be “Trip Report.”\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="522" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966708">Advanced</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. On the portal home page, select “Advanced” for show a drop-down menu containing the following items:\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        a. Contracts\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        b. Delivery Orders\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        c. Projects\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        d. Organizations\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="626" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966709">Resources</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. In the middle of the Travel Portal Home Page, you’ll see the Resources Menu.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        2. In this menu, the user can view GSA Per Diem Rates, Airport Codes, and Google Maps.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="293" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        3. I selected “Google Maps” as an example.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <img width="624" height="307" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h1>\r\n        <a name="_Toc391966710">Screen Options</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n    <p>\r\n        1. For complete customizability, the user is able to customize the screen display to his/her preference.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <br/>\r\n        <img width="584" height="331" src=""/>\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br clear="all"/>\r\n<h1>\r\n    <a name="_Toc391966711">+New</a>\r\n</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <p>\r\n            If the user would like to add a new post, add new media, or select a Travel Request Review, then the +New option is the menu you would utilize.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n    <img width="624" height="321" src=""/>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n    <a name="_Toc391966712">New Post</a>\r\n</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <p>\r\n            Select “Post.”\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n    <img width="625" height="315" src=""/>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n    <a name="_Toc391966713">New Media</a>\r\n</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <p>\r\n            Select “New Media” to be able to upload documentation and/or drop files to be uploaded.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <p>\r\n            <img width="624" height="300" src=""/>\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', 'User''s Manual', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2014-07-01 12:30:28', '2014-07-01 12:30:28', '', 0, 'http://dev.webtravelportal.net/?page_id=293', 0, 'page', '', 0),
